refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
mixedarray_reduce arrayinput callbackfunction intinitial
array_reduce applies iteratively the function function to the elements of the array input, so as to reduce the array to a single value.

&reftitle.returnvalues;
Returns the resulting value.
If the array is empty and initial is not passed, array_reduce returns &null;.

  &reftitle.examples;



    array_reduce example


<?php
function rsum($v, $w)
{
    $v += $w;
    return $v;
}

function rmul($v, $w)
{
    $v *= $w;
    return $v;
}

$a = array(1, 2, 3, 4, 5);
$x = array();
$b = array_reduce($a, "rsum");
$c = array_reduce($a, "rmul", 10);
$d = array_reduce($x, "rsum", 1);
?>




     This will result in $b containing
     15, $c containing
     1200 (= 10*1*2*3*4*5), and $d
     containing 1.
